result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

03:23 PM Defendant Autumn Patricia Kemnitz appeared by video means from Marquette County Jail. Prosecuting Atty Clifford C. Burdon appeared for State of Wisconsin.
  Defendant received a copy of the criminal complaint.    Court confirms address and phone.    Court finds probable cause for the charges for Riverside purposes.
  Court advises defendant of right to an attorney.  Defendant understands.
Defendant has not heard from her Attorney on her other cases yet.  

Atty Burdon requests a $5,000 cash bond with conditions.  Atty Burdon states that the defendant has an open case in Sauk County that she failed to appear on February 3rd in which a warrant was issued.
Defendant ran out of gas on the way there and she did try to contact her Attorney.

BY THE COURT:  Court sets a $1,000 Cash bond with conditions:
*No use or possession of any controlled substance without a valid prescription  Initial appearance scheduled for February 28, 2022 at 10:00 am.
